<concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="topic_4_3_6_4">
   <title>backuptbl</title>
   <conbody>
      <parml>
         <plentry>
            <pt>
               <codeph>backuptbl [start|commit|rollback] &lt;table_name&gt;</codeph>
            </pt>
            <pd>The backuptbl action allows you to back up a table. You must use this action in
          conjunction with a standard backup tool and the atquery utility. For more information, see
            <xref href="c_admin_guide-5_2_1-Backing-Up-and-Resto_snsg.xml#topic_5_2_1"/>.
            <codeblock xml:space="preserve"><codeph>backuptbl [start|commit|rollback] &lt;<i>table_name</i>&gt;</codeph></codeblock>
               <p>This
            action has three arguments:</p>
               <ul id="ul_j3p_b15_vx">
                  <li>
                     <codeph>start</codeph>—begins the backup session</li>
                  <li>
                     <codeph>commit</codeph>—commits the changes</li>
                  <li>
                     <codeph>rollback</codeph>—returns the table data to its pre-backup state</li>
               </ul>
            </pd>
         </plentry>
      </parml>
   </conbody>
</concept>